<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="b1947_03_00_an_SraffaPiero"><teiHeader><fileDesc> <titleStmt> <title>Von <persName key="WittgensteinLudwig" role="sender" full="yes">Ludwig Wittgenstein</persName> an <persName key="SraffaPiero" role="recipient" full="yes">Piero Sraffa</persName>, März 1947</title> <author>Wittgenstein, Ludwig</author> </titleStmt> <editionStmt n="bw2"> <edition>2. Auflage</edition> </editionStmt> <publicationStmt> <p>Ludwig Wittgenstein: Gesamtbriefwechsel, 2. Auflage</p> </publicationStmt> <sourceDesc default="false"> <p>Abschrift McGuinness, Kopie in BA.</p> </sourceDesc> </fileDesc><encodingDesc><p>TEI P5</p></encodingDesc><revisionDesc><list type="simple"><item>2010/05/15: Added to the collection</item><item>2018/12: Added to Innsbruck Correspondence Edition</item></list></revisionDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div type="transcript" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"> <div type="address" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="right">Trinity College </p> <p rend="right">Tuesday </p> </div> <div type="maintext" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="left">Dear Sraffa,</p> <p rend="indent">I tried to ring up your mother today because I wanted to see her before leaving for Swansea. The maid told me your mother was at the nursing home &amp; had an operation. Would you, if you find time, let me know what it was &amp; how she is. As I don’t know anything about it, I don’t know if she can, &amp; wants to, see visitors. I intend to leave Cambridge on Monday. If I can see your mother, please let me know <hi rend="underline">when</hi>.</p> <p rend="indent">Yours </p> <p rend="indent">L. Wittgenstein </p> </div> </div></body></text></TEI>